procedures.name: Blood Sampling
procedures.label: Blood Draw
procedures.description: Collection of blood samples for pharmacokinetic (PK), pharmacodynamic (PD), and clinical safety laboratory assessments (serum chemistry, hematology, coagulation).

code.decode: Collection of venous blood by venipuncture

procedures.name: 24-hour Urine Collection
procedures.label: 24h Urine Collection
procedures.description: Collection of all urine over a 24-hour period for measurement of copper and molybdenum content.

code.decode: Volume measurement for timed collection, each

procedures.name: Fecal Collection
procedures.label: Stool Sample Collection
procedures.description: Collection of individual fecal samples for measurement of copper and molybdenum content.

procedures.name: Physical Examination
procedures.label: Physical Exam
procedures.description: A full physical examination including assessments of the cardiovascular, respiratory, gastrointestinal, and neurological systems. Height and weight are also measured.

code.decode: Office or other outpatient visit for the evaluation and management of an established patient

procedures.name: Vital Signs Measurement
procedures.label: Vital Signs
procedures.description: Assessment of body temperature, heart rate, respiratory rate, and systolic and diastolic blood pressure.

procedures.name: 12-lead Electrocardiogram
procedures.label: ECG
procedures.description: Triplicate 12-lead ECG to assess heart rate, intervals (PR, QRS, QT and QTc), and other clinically significant findings.

code.decode: Electrocardiogram, routine ECG with at least 12 leads; with interpretation and report

procedures.name: Oral Drug Administration
procedures.label: Dosing
procedures.description: Administration of ALXN1840 tablets (15 mg or 30 mg) once daily with 240 mL of water after an overnight fast.

procedures.name: Urinalysis
procedures.label: Urinalysis
procedures.description: Laboratory analysis of a urine sample for diagnostic purposes.

code.decode: Urinalysis, by dip stick or tablet reagent for bilirubin, glucose, hemoglobin, ketones, leukocytes, nitrite, pH, protein, specific gravity, urobilinogen, any number of these constituents; automated, with microscopy

procedures.name: Pregnancy Test
procedures.label: Pregnancy Test
procedures.description: Urine or serum pregnancy test for women of childbearing potential.

code.decode: Urine pregnancy test, by visual color comparison methods

procedures.name: Food and Fluid Collection
procedures.label: Dietary Sample Collection
procedures.description: Collection of samples from all meal and fluid batches for measurement of copper and molybdenum content.

procedures.name: Urine Drug Screen
procedures.label: Urine Drug Screen
procedures.description: Screening of urine for the presence of disallowed drugs.

procedures.name: Alcohol Test
procedures.label: Alcohol Test
procedures.description: Test to screen for alcohol use.

procedures.name: HIV, Hepatitis B and C Screen
procedures.label: Viral Screen
procedures.description: Blood test to screen for Human Immunodeficiency Virus, Hepatitis B, and Hepatitis C.

procedures.name: Intravenous Cannula Placement
procedures.label: IV Cannula Placement
procedures.description: Placement of an intravenous cannula to minimize needle sticks for repeated blood draws.

code.decode: Introduction of needle or intracatheter, vein

procedures.name: Adverse Event Monitoring
procedures.label: AE Monitoring
procedures.description: Ongoing monitoring and collection of information on adverse events (AEs) and serious adverse events (SAEs).

medicalDevices.name: Intravenous Cannula
medicalDevices.label: IV Cannula
medicalDevices.description: A cannula placed in a vein to allow for repeated blood draws while minimizing needle sticks.

medicalDevices.name: Automated Blood Pressure Device
medicalDevices.label: Automated BP Monitor
medicalDevices.description: A completely automated device for assessing blood pressure and heart rate.

medicalDevices.name: 12-lead ECG Machine
medicalDevices.label: ECG Machine
medicalDevices.description: Device used to perform triplicate 12-lead electrocardiograms.

medicalDevices.name: Inductively Coupled Plasma Mass Spectrometry
medicalDevices.label: ICP-MS
medicalDevices.description: An analytical instrument used to determine the copper and molybdenum concentration of food, fluid, urine, and fecal samples.
